---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import AngleExplorer from '../../../components/diagrams/AngleExplorer.svelte';
---

<Layout title="Angles" lang="en" backHref="/explore-math/en/grade-6/" backLabel="← Grade 6">
	<h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Angles</h1>
	<p class="text-lg text-slate-600 mb-8">Measure, draw and calculate angles</p>

	<section class="prose max-w-none">
		<h2>What is an angle?</h2>
		<p>An angle is formed when two rays meet at a point. We measure angles in <strong>degrees (°)</strong>. A full rotation = 360°.</p>

		<h3>🧪 Experiment: Discover Angle Types</h3>
		<p>Drag the slider and observe how the angle changes. At what degrees does the angle type change?</p>
	</section>

	<AngleExplorer client:visible />

	<section class="prose max-w-none mt-8">
		<h3>💡 Types of Angles</h3>
		<ul>
			<li><strong>Acute angle:</strong> 0° to 90°</li>
			<li><strong>Right angle:</strong> exactly 90°</li>
			<li><strong>Obtuse angle:</strong> 90° to 180°</li>
			<li><strong>Straight angle:</strong> exactly 180°</li>
			<li><strong>Reflex angle:</strong> 180° to 360°</li>
		</ul>
		<p>Supplementary angles add up to 180°. Vertical angles are equal!</p>
	</section>
</Layout>
